Fingerprint Unlock
Fingerprint Unlock creates a unique model of your fingerprint to verify it’s you. To create this fingerprint model during setup, you will take images of your fingerprint from different positions.

When you use Fingerprint Unlock, images are used to update your fingerprint model. Images used to create your fingerprint model are never stored, but the fingerprint model is stored securely on your phone and never leaves the phone. All processing occurs securely on your phone.
You can delete your fingerprint model, or turn off Fingerprint Unlock at any time in Settings. Fingerprint models are stored on the phone until you delete them.

Fingerprint Unlock creates a unique model of your child’s fingerprint to verify it’s them. To create this fingerprint model during setup, they will take images of their fingerprint from different positions.

When they use Fingerprint Unlock, images are used to update their fingerprint model. Images used to create your child’s fingerprint model are never stored, but the fingerprint model is stored securely on the phone and never leaves the phone. All processing occurs securely on the phone.
You and your child can delete their fingerprint model, or turn off Fingerprint Unlock at any time in Settings. Fingerprint models are stored on the phone until they’re deleted.
